{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01QrV2W1Nk1DXt7NuGvZsRZZ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Evaluator Super Agent\n2\t\n3\tEvan's primary assignment: build an evaluation agent that automates prototype quality assessment within the [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) pipeline.\n4\t\n5\t**Status: Shipped.** The evaluator is a 3-phase skill pipeline on branch `evan/prototype-evaluate` at [andybraren/prototype-creator](https://github.com/andybraren/prototype-creator). It has evaluated 18+ STRATs against Jira acceptance criteria with Playwright persona walkthroughs.\n6\t\n7\t## What It Does (current)\n8\t\n9\t| Capability | Source | Status |\n10\t|---|---|---|\n11\t| AC evaluation | Custom Playwright persona journeys against Jira criteria | Shipped |\n12\t| Usability scoring | 7-dimension rubric with persona overlays (Zack Bodnar's framework) | Shipped |\n13\t| Consistency checking | Beau Morley's consistency checker (source + visual mode) | Shipped |\n14\t| Navigation reachability | Playwright verifies pages are clickable from sidebar | Shipped |\n15\t| Human review | Review tab in HTML report with override buttons + CSV writeback | Shipped |\n16\t| Report hosting | GitLab Pages (eval-reports-7ebc0e.pages.redhat.com) | Shipped |\n17\t| Google Sheet sync | Automated pass/fail + usability metrics to tracking sheet | Shipped |\n18\t| Feedback loop | Eval results → prototype-refine → re-eval (max 3 iterations) | In progress |\n19\t\n20\t## Architecture (confirmed June 16 with Andy)\n21\t\n22\tEvolved from \"single monolithic super agent\" to a **phased pipeline with overlays**:\n23\t\n24\t```\n25\tPhase 1: prototype-evaluate (extract ACs, RFE, Outcome, personas, journeys)\n26\t    ↓ writes extract-state.json\n27\tPhase 2: evaluate-journey (Playwright walkthroughs, consistency check)\n28\t    ↓ writes journey-log.json, screenshots, CSV\n29\tPhase 3: evaluate-usability (7-dimension persona scoring)\n30\t    ↓ updates journey-log.json\n31\tPhase 4: render-report.js + sync-sheet.js (HTML, CSV, Google Sheet)\n32\t```\n33\t\n34\t**Key design decisions:**\n35\t1. **Outcomes over Strategic Goals** as grounding criteria (Outcomes are consistently written)\n36\t2. **One Playwright pass** — shared screenshots across usability, consistency, and AC checks\n37\t3. **98% generic + 2% product overlay** (`config/product-overlay.yaml`) — portable to other products\n38\t4. **Hint mechanism** for dead-end navigation (failure logged but journey continues)\n39\t5. **Human-in-the-loop** — Review tab for designer input before feedback loop acts\n40\t\n41\t## Research References\n42\t\n43\t- **Avenir-UX** — autonomous UX evaluation agent using SEQ/SUS + persona framework\n44\t- **UXCascade** — multi-agent persona simulation with severity-rated issues (S1–S4)\n45\t- GitLab Notes REST API for MR comment posting\n46\t- Danger bot framework for CI-integrated review automation\n47\t\n48\t## How It Connects\n49\t\n50\t```\n51\tJira STRAT (Outcome → RFE → STRAT)\n52\t    → prototype-create (generates code in workspace)\n53\t    → prototype-evaluate (this agent — 3 phases)\n54\t        ├── Phase 1: Extract ACs, personas, journeys from Jira\n55\t        ├── Phase 2: Playwright journeys + consistency check\n56\t        ├── Phase 3: Usability dimension scoring\n57\t        └── Phase 4: Report + Sheet sync\n58\t    → Human reviews report (override verdicts, add notes)\n59\t    → prototype-refine (acts on suggestions + human annotations)\n60\t    → Re-evaluate (loop until PASS or max iterations)\n61\t    → prototype-submit (MR to GitLab)\n62\t```\n63\t\n64\t## Key Design Inputs from Demo (May 14)\n65\t\n66\tFrom the [Prototype Creator Demo](prototype-creator-demo-may14.md):\n67\t- Consistency checkers should only evaluate what's NEW (CSS class=\"new\" tagging)\n68\t- Even auto-mode should produce decision-kit pages for post-review\n69\t- Evaluator needs outcome-level awareness, not just feature-level\n70\t- Preview URL is the evaluation entry point (load the MR URL, assess in browser context)\n71\t- Token efficiency matters — scope evaluation to changed areas only\n72\t\n73\t## Related\n74\t\n75\t- [Outcome Tiger Team](outcome-tiger-team.md) — proposes outcome-level awareness for evaluation, directly extending this agent's scope\n76\t- [Prototype Creator Demo — May 14](prototype-creator-demo-may14.md) — walkthrough with design insights for this agent\n77\t- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) — the pipeline this plugs into\n78\t- [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md) — existing scoring to extend\n79\t- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) — pattern for automated eval loops\n80\t- [Decision Kit](decision-kit.md) — using /strategize to plan this agent\n81\t- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) — informs methodology choice\n82\t- [My Cursor Claw](my-cursor-claw.md) — the workspace where this will be built\n83\t- [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy — 2026-06-17](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) — heuristic eval pilot connects to automated evaluation vision\n84\t\n85\t## Updates from June 16, 2026 Review\n86\t\n87\tDecisions made with Andy Braren (see [Andy/Evan Eval Review — June 16](andy-evan-eval-review-2026-06-16.md)):\n88\t\n89\t- **Architecture confirmed:** Centralized super evaluator, not fragmented skills. One Playwright pass, shared screenshots.\n90\t- **Grounding confirmed:** Outcomes as primary criteria, Strategic Goals excluded for now.\n91\t- **Overlay approach adopted:** 98% generic + 2% product-specific layer. See [GitLab skill-overlays best practice](https://gitlab.cee.redhat.com/global-engineering/wg-agentic-sdlc/-/blob/main/best-practices/skill-overlays.md).\n92\t- **Hint mechanism shipped:** Simulated UX researcher provides next URL on failure, allowing evaluation to continue while logging failure impact.\n93\t- **Screenshot consolidation:** Sub-agents share one set of Playwright screenshots instead of each capturing independently.\n94\t\n95\t- [RH AI-First UX — 2026-06-18](rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-18.md) — Evan demoed automated usability testing + PatternFly consistency checker to full team\n96\t- [Andy/Evan Meeting — June 22](andy-evan-2026-06-22.md) — eval iteration history, flagging system, Prototype Creator integration strategy\n97\t- [AI-First Sync — June 25](ai-first-sync-2026-06-25.md) — Evan's full evaluator presentation to the team, readiness check discussion\n98\t- [RH AI-First UX — June 25](rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-25.md) — testing fragmentation concerns, unified testing proposal\n99\t- [Standup — June 29](standup-2026-06-29.md) — 2 automated usability testing agents in development\n100\t- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) — context engineering technique relevant to team-specific overlays\n101\t- [Andy/Evan Meeting — June 29](andy-evan-2026-06-29.md) — findings tab, auto-fix vs report-only modes, X-ray vs blind evaluation, centralized dashboard\n102\t- [Midpoint Check-in — June 30](midpoint-checkin-2026-06-30.md) — Zack: \"pioneering work\" combining research + AI + SDLC; report must be immediately actionable for designers\n103\t\n104\t## Sources\n105\t\n106\t- [Andy/Evan Eval Review — June 16](andy-evan-eval-review-2026-06-16.md)\n107\t- Andy/Evan meeting notes — 2026-06-08\n108\t- sources/2026-06-09-prototype-creator-overview.html\n109\t- /strategize session — 2026-06-09 (in progress)\n110\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f9a3ce62-434a-4f59-920a-2c5c141fc64e","uuid":"91051cf0-2e3c-44d4-942b-1a68922be904","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:35:05.521Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/evaluator-super-agent.md","content":"# Evaluator Super Agent\n\nEvan's primary assignment: build an evaluation agent that automates prototype quality assessment within the [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) pipeline.\n\n**Status: Shipped.** The evaluator is a 3-phase skill pipeline on branch `evan/prototype-evaluate` at [andybraren/prototype-creator](https://github.com/andybraren/prototype-creator). It has evaluated 18+ STRATs against Jira acceptance criteria with Playwright persona walkthroughs.\n\n## What It Does (current)\n\n| Capability | Source | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| AC evaluation | Custom Playwright persona journeys against Jira criteria | Shipped |\n| Usability scoring | 7-dimension rubric with persona overlays (Zack Bodnar's framework) | Shipped |\n| Consistency checking | Beau Morley's consistency checker (source + visual mode) | Shipped |\n| Navigation reachability | Playwright verifies pages are clickable from sidebar | Shipped |\n| Human review | Review tab in HTML report with override buttons + CSV writeback | Shipped |\n| Report hosting | GitLab Pages (eval-reports-7ebc0e.pages.redhat.com) | Shipped |\n| Google Sheet sync | Automated pass/fail + usability metrics to tracking sheet | Shipped |\n| Feedback loop | Eval results → prototype-refine → re-eval (max 3 iterations) | In progress |\n\n## Architecture (confirmed June 16 with Andy)\n\nEvolved from \"single monolithic super agent\" to a **phased pipeline with overlays**:\n\n```\nPhase 1: prototype-evaluate (extract ACs, RFE, Outcome, personas, journeys)\n    ↓ writes extract-state.json\nPhase 2: evaluate-journey (Playwright walkthroughs, consistency check)\n    ↓ writes journey-log.json, screenshots, CSV\nPhase 3: evaluate-usability (7-dimension persona scoring)\n    ↓ updates journey-log.json\nPhase 4: render-report.js + sync-sheet.js (HTML, CSV, Google Sheet)\n```\n\n**Key design decisions:**\n1. **Outcomes over Strategic Goals** as grounding criteria (Outcomes are consistently written)\n2. **One Playwright pass** — shared screenshots across usability, consistency, and AC checks\n3. **98% generic + 2% product overlay** (`config/product-overlay.yaml`) — portable to other products\n4. **Hint mechanism** for dead-end navigation (failure logged but journey continues)\n5. **Human-in-the-loop** — Review tab for designer input before feedback loop acts\n\n## Research References\n\n- **Avenir-UX** — autonomous UX evaluation agent using SEQ/SUS + persona framework\n- **UXCascade** — multi-agent persona simulation with severity-rated issues (S1–S4)\n- GitLab Notes REST API for MR comment posting\n- Danger bot framework for CI-integrated review automation\n\n## How It Connects\n\n```\nJira STRAT (Outcome → RFE → STRAT)\n    → prototype-create (generates code in workspace)\n    → prototype-evaluate (this agent — 3 phases)\n        ├── Phase 1: Extract ACs, personas, journeys from Jira\n        ├── Phase 2: Playwright journeys + consistency check\n        ├── Phase 3: Usability dimension scoring\n        └── Phase 4: Report + Sheet sync\n    → Human reviews report (override verdicts, add notes)\n    → prototype-refine (acts on suggestions + human annotations)\n    → Re-evaluate (loop until PASS or max iterations)\n    → prototype-submit (MR to GitLab)\n```\n\n## Key Design Inputs from Demo (May 14)\n\nFrom the [Prototype Creator Demo](prototype-creator-demo-may14.md):\n- Consistency checkers should only evaluate what's NEW (CSS class=\"new\" tagging)\n- Even auto-mode should produce decision-kit pages for post-review\n- Evaluator needs outcome-level awareness, not just feature-level\n- Preview URL is the evaluation entry point (load the MR URL, assess in browser context)\n- Token efficiency matters — scope evaluation to changed areas only\n\n## Related\n\n- [Outcome Tiger Team](outcome-tiger-team.md) — proposes outcome-level awareness for evaluation, directly extending this agent's scope\n- [Prototype Creator Demo — May 14](prototype-creator-demo-may14.md) — walkthrough with design insights for this agent\n- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) — the pipeline this plugs into\n- [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md) — existing scoring to extend\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) — pattern for automated eval loops\n- [Decision Kit](decision-kit.md) — using /strategize to plan this agent\n- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) — informs methodology choice\n- [My Cursor Claw](my-cursor-claw.md) — the workspace where this will be built\n- [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy — 2026-06-17](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) — heuristic eval pilot connects to automated evaluation vision\n\n## Updates from June 16, 2026 Review\n\nDecisions made with Andy Braren (see [Andy/Evan Eval Review — June 16](andy-evan-eval-review-2026-06-16.md)):\n\n- **Architecture confirmed:** Centralized super evaluator, not fragmented skills. One Playwright pass, shared screenshots.\n- **Grounding confirmed:** Outcomes as primary criteria, Strategic Goals excluded for now.\n- **Overlay approach adopted:** 98% generic + 2% product-specific layer. See [GitLab skill-overlays best practice](https://gitlab.cee.redhat.com/global-engineering/wg-agentic-sdlc/-/blob/main/best-practices/skill-overlays.md).\n- **Hint mechanism shipped:** Simulated UX researcher provides next URL on failure, allowing evaluation to continue while logging failure impact.\n- **Screenshot consolidation:** Sub-agents share one set of Playwright screenshots instead of each capturing independently.\n\n- [RH AI-First UX — 2026-06-18](rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-18.md) — Evan demoed automated usability testing + PatternFly consistency checker to full team\n- [Andy/Evan Meeting — June 22](andy-evan-2026-06-22.md) — eval iteration history, flagging system, Prototype Creator integration strategy\n- [AI-First Sync — June 25](ai-first-sync-2026-06-25.md) — Evan's full evaluator presentation to the team, readiness check discussion\n- [RH AI-First UX — June 25](rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-25.md) — testing fragmentation concerns, unified testing proposal\n- [Standup — June 29](standup-2026-06-29.md) — 2 automated usability testing agents in development\n- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) — context engineering technique relevant to team-specific overlays\n- [Andy/Evan Meeting — June 29](andy-evan-2026-06-29.md) — findings tab, auto-fix vs report-only modes, X-ray vs blind evaluation, centralized dashboard\n- [Midpoint Check-in — June 30](midpoint-checkin-2026-06-30.md) — Zack: \"pioneering work\" combining research + AI + SDLC; report must be immediately actionable for designers\n\n## Sources\n\n- [Andy/Evan Eval Review — June 16](andy-evan-eval-review-2026-06-16.md)\n- Andy/Evan meeting notes — 2026-06-08\n- sources/2026-06-09-prototype-creator-overview.html\n- /strategize session — 2026-06-09 (in progress)\n","numLines":110,"startLine":1,"totalLines":110}}}
