{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_018Gx2roFSE7GggwVfRXa6Cy","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# UX Quality Rubric\n2\t\n3\tThe scoring system used by [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) to evaluate generated prototypes. Scored by a restricted `prototype-scorer` agent (no shell, no network, no MCP).\n4\t\n5\t## Dimensions (0–2 each, 8 total)\n6\t\n7\t| Dimension | What It Measures |\n8\t|---|---|\n9\t| **Completeness** | Does the prototype cover the RFE's user stories and acceptance criteria? |\n10\t| **Usability** | Is the interaction pattern clear and free of obvious friction? (Nielsen's 10 heuristics) |\n11\t| **Feasibility** | Can this be built with the target design system (PatternFly 6)? |\n12\t| **Fidelity Match** | Does the prototype match the requested fidelity level — not over or under-engineered? |\n13\t\n14\t## Pass Threshold\n15\t\n16\t6+ total with no zeros. Prototypes scoring above get `prototype-creator-rubric-pass`. Below get `prototype-creator-needs-attention`.\n17\t\n18\t## Scoring Agent\n19\t\n20\tOne invocation per dimension ensures scores are deterministic and auditable. The scorer agent is restricted — no shell, no network, no MCP — to prevent contamination.\n21\t\n22\t## Connection to Evaluator Super Agent\n23\t\n24\tThe [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) will extend this rubric with additional dimensions from simulated usability and desirability testing. See also [Nielsen's Heuristics](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) for the research that informs the usability dimension.\n25\t\n26\t## Related\n27\t\n28\t- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) — the pipeline that uses this rubric\n29\t- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) — extends this scoring\n30\t- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) — informs the usability dimension\n31\t- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) — similar pattern of rubric-based automated scoring\n32\t\n33\t## Sources\n34\t\n35\t- sources/2026-06-09-prototype-creator-overview.html\n36\t- andybraren/prototype-creator config/ux-rubric.yaml\n37\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f9a3ce62-434a-4f59-920a-2c5c141fc64e","uuid":"258d9124-ff1f-4bab-a3a6-132652b656f8","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:35:05.913Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/ux-quality-rubric.md","content":"# UX Quality Rubric\n\nThe scoring system used by [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) to evaluate generated prototypes. Scored by a restricted `prototype-scorer` agent (no shell, no network, no MCP).\n\n## Dimensions (0–2 each, 8 total)\n\n| Dimension | What It Measures |\n|---|---|\n| **Completeness** | Does the prototype cover the RFE's user stories and acceptance criteria? |\n| **Usability** | Is the interaction pattern clear and free of obvious friction? (Nielsen's 10 heuristics) |\n| **Feasibility** | Can this be built with the target design system (PatternFly 6)? |\n| **Fidelity Match** | Does the prototype match the requested fidelity level — not over or under-engineered? |\n\n## Pass Threshold\n\n6+ total with no zeros. Prototypes scoring above get `prototype-creator-rubric-pass`. Below get `prototype-creator-needs-attention`.\n\n## Scoring Agent\n\nOne invocation per dimension ensures scores are deterministic and auditable. The scorer agent is restricted — no shell, no network, no MCP — to prevent contamination.\n\n## Connection to Evaluator Super Agent\n\nThe [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) will extend this rubric with additional dimensions from simulated usability and desirability testing. See also [Nielsen's Heuristics](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) for the research that informs the usability dimension.\n\n## Related\n\n- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) — the pipeline that uses this rubric\n- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) — extends this scoring\n- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) — informs the usability dimension\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) — similar pattern of rubric-based automated scoring\n\n## Sources\n\n- sources/2026-06-09-prototype-creator-overview.html\n- andybraren/prototype-creator config/ux-rubric.yaml\n","numLines":37,"startLine":1,"totalLines":37}}}
