{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01D5aYo7FJaCLPU4xV8p4HoH","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Standup -- June 29, 2026\n2\t\n3\tTeam standup for Future Sustainability & E2E. Usability testing updates, UX debt prioritization, and research tooling.\n4\t\n5\t## Key Points\n6\t\n7\t- **Usability testing RFC approved:** Team approved Request for Comments on usability testing flow.\n8\t- **3.5 UX debt:** Leaders mandated identifying 1 critical UX debt item per team for 3.5 release.\n9\t- **Research tooling:** Development continues on observability dashboards and 2 automated usability testing agents. Research insight tool (Archie/UFD) now supports live data extraction via CLI.\n10\t- **Testing scope:** Models of service admin persona for 3.4 release testing. Engineering consumption testing deferred to 3.5.\n11\t- **Sovereign Cloud:** Work commenced on Sovereign Cloud prototypes and continuous customer feedback pipelines.\n12\t- **Sprint capacity:** Emphasis on realistic workload distribution for current cycle.\n13\t\n14\t## Next Steps\n15\t\n16\t- Yingzhao: Finalize RFC items in Jira, set up observability dashboards, iterate on usability comparison approach\n17\t- Jenn: Share engineering Kanban link, provide 3.5 release schedule, create tenant admin user flows for sovereign cloud\n18\t- Yahav: Create formal proposal for usability testing agents in AI development lifecycle, publish Archie update to helper repo\n19\t\n20\t## Related\n21\t\n22\t- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) -- automated usability testing agents referenced\n23\t- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) -- usability comparison approach\n24\t- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) -- sovereign cloud prototypes\n25\t\n26\t## Sources\n27\t\n28\t- ~/Desktop/Notes Inbox/gemini-2026-06-29-standup---future-sustainability-e2e---20260629-1259-edt---notes-by-gemini.txt\n29\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f9a3ce62-434a-4f59-920a-2c5c141fc64e","uuid":"ff87365b-3555-4b0b-a5be-eeb4f3370dba","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:35:06.557Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/standup-2026-06-29.md","content":"# Standup -- June 29, 2026\n\nTeam standup for Future Sustainability & E2E. Usability testing updates, UX debt prioritization, and research tooling.\n\n## Key Points\n\n- **Usability testing RFC approved:** Team approved Request for Comments on usability testing flow.\n- **3.5 UX debt:** Leaders mandated identifying 1 critical UX debt item per team for 3.5 release.\n- **Research tooling:** Development continues on observability dashboards and 2 automated usability testing agents. Research insight tool (Archie/UFD) now supports live data extraction via CLI.\n- **Testing scope:** Models of service admin persona for 3.4 release testing. Engineering consumption testing deferred to 3.5.\n- **Sovereign Cloud:** Work commenced on Sovereign Cloud prototypes and continuous customer feedback pipelines.\n- **Sprint capacity:** Emphasis on realistic workload distribution for current cycle.\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Yingzhao: Finalize RFC items in Jira, set up observability dashboards, iterate on usability comparison approach\n- Jenn: Share engineering Kanban link, provide 3.5 release schedule, create tenant admin user flows for sovereign cloud\n- Yahav: Create formal proposal for usability testing agents in AI development lifecycle, publish Archie update to helper repo\n\n## Related\n\n- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) -- automated usability testing agents referenced\n- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) -- usability comparison approach\n- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) -- sovereign cloud prototypes\n\n## Sources\n\n- ~/Desktop/Notes Inbox/gemini-2026-06-29-standup---future-sustainability-e2e---20260629-1259-edt---notes-by-gemini.txt\n","numLines":29,"startLine":1,"totalLines":29}}}
