{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01UMDqKBycXV68byiM6CwTfz","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# RH AI-First UX -- June 25, 2026\n2\t\n3\tWeekly AI-first UX team meeting covering Outcome Creator, testing strategy, and infrastructure alignment.\n4\t\n5\t## Key Discussion Points\n6\t\n7\t- **Outcome Creator JTBD integration:** Yahav tested Jobs to be Done data in Outcome Creator. Successfully linked specific jobs to outcomes. Bug: skill writes artifact files to project root instead of workspace.\n8\t- **Personnel update:** Beau on medical leave for several months. Team adjusting Kiwi-related work.\n9\t- **Quality Engineering transition:** QE team transitioning under Ron's management. Yahav got handover doc with context on UXD-within-QE initiative. Kamesh facilitating intro.\n10\t- **Agentic CI and skill orchestration:** Need for a higher-level orchestrator that determines which skills are executed within the RHAI pipeline. Zack shared \"Agentic CI\" docs (library for packaging skills into agentic packages).\n11\t- **Infrastructure standardization:** Lack of clarity in mapping between different infrastructure concepts (blue box, implementation zone). UIE aims to standardize.\n12\t- **Models of service outcomes:** Andy used Outcome Creator for models of service/inference outcomes. Planning to present at PM-wide meeting next Wednesday. PMs appreciated JTBD data integration.\n13\t- **Testing fragmentation:** Zack flagged proliferation of varied prototype/usability testing tools across the org (Yonyi's team, prototype evaluator, heuristic analysis skills). Team needs to establish canonical version or unified standard.\n14\t- **Unified testing proposal:** Yahav assigned to draft formal proposal for review next week defining dimensions and requirements for standard usability testing approach.\n15\t- **Artifact storage pattern:** Team agreed to establish a common design pattern for storing project artifacts consistently across all skills.\n16\t\n17\t## Decisions\n18\t\n19\t- Common artifact storage pattern to be established across skills\n20\t- Unified usability testing strategy proposal to be drafted\n21\t- Journeys and milestones reside within outcome level in Jira architecture\n22\t\n23\t## Related\n24\t\n25\t- [Outcome Tiger Team](outcome-tiger-team.md) -- outcome creator progress and JTBD integration\n26\t- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) -- part of the testing fragmentation discussion\n27\t- [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md) -- agentic CI and skill orchestration\n28\t- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) -- artifact storage pattern\n29\t- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) -- unified testing strategy context\n30\t\n31\t## Sources\n32\t\n33\t- ~/Desktop/Notes Inbox/gemini-2026-06-25-rh-ai-first-ux---20260625-1600-edt---notes-by-gemini.txt\n34\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f9a3ce62-434a-4f59-920a-2c5c141fc64e","uuid":"9dca639e-2a2e-417b-9aaf-3718a70c2414","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:35:12.986Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-25.md","content":"# RH AI-First UX -- June 25, 2026\n\nWeekly AI-first UX team meeting covering Outcome Creator, testing strategy, and infrastructure alignment.\n\n## Key Discussion Points\n\n- **Outcome Creator JTBD integration:** Yahav tested Jobs to be Done data in Outcome Creator. Successfully linked specific jobs to outcomes. Bug: skill writes artifact files to project root instead of workspace.\n- **Personnel update:** Beau on medical leave for several months. Team adjusting Kiwi-related work.\n- **Quality Engineering transition:** QE team transitioning under Ron's management. Yahav got handover doc with context on UXD-within-QE initiative. Kamesh facilitating intro.\n- **Agentic CI and skill orchestration:** Need for a higher-level orchestrator that determines which skills are executed within the RHAI pipeline. Zack shared \"Agentic CI\" docs (library for packaging skills into agentic packages).\n- **Infrastructure standardization:** Lack of clarity in mapping between different infrastructure concepts (blue box, implementation zone). UIE aims to standardize.\n- **Models of service outcomes:** Andy used Outcome Creator for models of service/inference outcomes. Planning to present at PM-wide meeting next Wednesday. PMs appreciated JTBD data integration.\n- **Testing fragmentation:** Zack flagged proliferation of varied prototype/usability testing tools across the org (Yonyi's team, prototype evaluator, heuristic analysis skills). Team needs to establish canonical version or unified standard.\n- **Unified testing proposal:** Yahav assigned to draft formal proposal for review next week defining dimensions and requirements for standard usability testing approach.\n- **Artifact storage pattern:** Team agreed to establish a common design pattern for storing project artifacts consistently across all skills.\n\n## Decisions\n\n- Common artifact storage pattern to be established across skills\n- Unified usability testing strategy proposal to be drafted\n- Journeys and milestones reside within outcome level in Jira architecture\n\n## Related\n\n- [Outcome Tiger Team](outcome-tiger-team.md) -- outcome creator progress and JTBD integration\n- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) -- part of the testing fragmentation discussion\n- [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md) -- agentic CI and skill orchestration\n- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) -- artifact storage pattern\n- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) -- unified testing strategy context\n\n## Sources\n\n- ~/Desktop/Notes Inbox/gemini-2026-06-25-rh-ai-first-ux---20260625-1600-edt---notes-by-gemini.txt\n","numLines":34,"startLine":1,"totalLines":34}}}
