{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01PVCHV93chJyhjJRw4ed1Tr","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Andy/Evan Meeting -- June 29, 2026\n2\t\n3\t1:1 covering prototype evaluator progress, reporting infrastructure, repository strategy, and future directions.\n4\t\n5\t## Key Discussion Points\n6\t\n7\t- **Persona walkthroughs separated:** Fixed overlap issue. Developing \"Findings\" tab documenting issues and resolutions. Implementing \"Auto-fix\" vs \"Report-only\" modes to manage regressions.\n8\t- **Data discrepancies:** Patient scores fluctuating without clear explanation. Investigating inconsistencies.\n9\t- **Jira entity confusion:** Clarified RF (Product Managers create) → Strat relationship. Prototype Creator should ideally link to RF (upstream). \"UI Direction\" section in Strat documents remains useful for prototyping.\n10\t- **Token optimization:** Configure AI to extract only necessary sections (e.g., \"UI Direction\") rather than ingesting entire Strat documents. Need to confirm if it's a hardcoded heading.\n11\t- **Report UX:** Avoid \"cockpit view\" information density. Prioritize error states and human review items top-left. Overview-first interface with drill-down.\n12\t- **Centralized dashboard:** Build homepage for evaluation reports with sorting, searching, filtering by date/time. Track common mistakes and average scores.\n13\t- **UXD PC7 cluster:** OpenShift cluster for internal validation and hosting. Potential containerized solution for reports/dashboards instead of GitLab pages.\n14\t- **Skill composability:** Evaluation skills must be designed for portability, not locked into Red Hat AI-specific contexts. UXD-level AI helpers repository is key.\n15\t- **X-ray vs blind modes:** Discussed evaluation with code visibility vs user-perspective-only modes. Persona evaluations currently run in parallel with fresh context windows.\n16\t- **Leaderboard of Pain:** Future concept using AI to synthesize cross-report research insights and identify top user pain points.\n17\t- **Archie integration:** Proposed automated system to ingest research notes, extract and assign points to pain points.\n18\t- **Internship scope:** Andy encouraged Evan to advocate for personal interests (traditional UX research/design) during midpoint check-in with Zack.\n19\t\n20\t## Decisions\n21\t\n22\t- PR organized into sub-skill structure, merged before eventual migration to centralized UXD repo\n23\t- Scripts placed in `scripts/` subdirectory following agentskills.io standard\n24\t\n25\t## Evan's Action Items\n26\t\n27\t- Modularize Prototype Creator into sub-skills\n28\t- Clean unused script files, comparative check against main branch\n29\t- Review agentskills.io documentation\n30\t- Investigate UXD PC7 cluster for hosting\n31\t- Watch hackathon recording for Leaderboard of Pain concept\n32\t- Consult Yahav about UX research representations and pain point tracking\n33\t- Prepare questions for upcoming Zack meeting (design/research exploration)\n34\t\n35\t## Related\n36\t\n37\t- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) -- direct progress update on evaluation architecture\n38\t- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) -- PR management, sub-skill structure, composability\n39\t- [Andy/Evan Meeting -- June 22](andy-evan-2026-06-22.md) -- previous 1:1 continuing same threads\n40\t- [AI-First Sync -- June 25](ai-first-sync-2026-06-25.md) -- earlier presentation of this work\n41\t- [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) -- UXD-level repo strategy\n42\t- [Outcome Tiger Team](outcome-tiger-team.md) -- Leaderboard of Pain concept connects to outcome-level awareness\n43\t\n44\t## Sources\n45\t\n46\t- ~/Desktop/Notes Inbox/gemini-2026-06-29-andy-evan---20260629-1432-edt---notes-by-gemini.txt\n47\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f9a3ce62-434a-4f59-920a-2c5c141fc64e","uuid":"2af4f7f8-6456-41fc-b988-7ab61c35ba05","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:35:13.084Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/andy-evan-2026-06-29.md","content":"# Andy/Evan Meeting -- June 29, 2026\n\n1:1 covering prototype evaluator progress, reporting infrastructure, repository strategy, and future directions.\n\n## Key Discussion Points\n\n- **Persona walkthroughs separated:** Fixed overlap issue. Developing \"Findings\" tab documenting issues and resolutions. Implementing \"Auto-fix\" vs \"Report-only\" modes to manage regressions.\n- **Data discrepancies:** Patient scores fluctuating without clear explanation. Investigating inconsistencies.\n- **Jira entity confusion:** Clarified RF (Product Managers create) → Strat relationship. Prototype Creator should ideally link to RF (upstream). \"UI Direction\" section in Strat documents remains useful for prototyping.\n- **Token optimization:** Configure AI to extract only necessary sections (e.g., \"UI Direction\") rather than ingesting entire Strat documents. Need to confirm if it's a hardcoded heading.\n- **Report UX:** Avoid \"cockpit view\" information density. Prioritize error states and human review items top-left. Overview-first interface with drill-down.\n- **Centralized dashboard:** Build homepage for evaluation reports with sorting, searching, filtering by date/time. Track common mistakes and average scores.\n- **UXD PC7 cluster:** OpenShift cluster for internal validation and hosting. Potential containerized solution for reports/dashboards instead of GitLab pages.\n- **Skill composability:** Evaluation skills must be designed for portability, not locked into Red Hat AI-specific contexts. UXD-level AI helpers repository is key.\n- **X-ray vs blind modes:** Discussed evaluation with code visibility vs user-perspective-only modes. Persona evaluations currently run in parallel with fresh context windows.\n- **Leaderboard of Pain:** Future concept using AI to synthesize cross-report research insights and identify top user pain points.\n- **Archie integration:** Proposed automated system to ingest research notes, extract and assign points to pain points.\n- **Internship scope:** Andy encouraged Evan to advocate for personal interests (traditional UX research/design) during midpoint check-in with Zack.\n\n## Decisions\n\n- PR organized into sub-skill structure, merged before eventual migration to centralized UXD repo\n- Scripts placed in `scripts/` subdirectory following agentskills.io standard\n\n## Evan's Action Items\n\n- Modularize Prototype Creator into sub-skills\n- Clean unused script files, comparative check against main branch\n- Review agentskills.io documentation\n- Investigate UXD PC7 cluster for hosting\n- Watch hackathon recording for Leaderboard of Pain concept\n- Consult Yahav about UX research representations and pain point tracking\n- Prepare questions for upcoming Zack meeting (design/research exploration)\n\n## Related\n\n- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) -- direct progress update on evaluation architecture\n- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) -- PR management, sub-skill structure, composability\n- [Andy/Evan Meeting -- June 22](andy-evan-2026-06-22.md) -- previous 1:1 continuing same threads\n- [AI-First Sync -- June 25](ai-first-sync-2026-06-25.md) -- earlier presentation of this work\n- [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) -- UXD-level repo strategy\n- [Outcome Tiger Team](outcome-tiger-team.md) -- Leaderboard of Pain concept connects to outcome-level awareness\n\n## Sources\n\n- ~/Desktop/Notes Inbox/gemini-2026-06-29-andy-evan---20260629-1432-edt---notes-by-gemini.txt\n","numLines":47,"startLine":1,"totalLines":47}}}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_0178wKP7cLYWMtrv21gNHk52", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Here's what your wiki knows about usability testing:\n\n---\n\n## Direct Matches\n\n**[Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md)** \u2014 your primary work on this topic.\n- Shipped a 3-phase automated usability testing pipeline on branch `evan/prototype-evaluate` that has evaluated 18+ STRATs\n- Architecture: Phase 1 (extract ACs/personas/journeys) \u2192 Phase 2 (Playwright walkthroughs + consistency check) \u2192 Phase 3 (7-dimension usability scoring) \u2192 Phase 4 (HTML report + Google Sheet sync)\n- Key design choices: Outcomes as grounding criteria (not Strategic Goals), one Playwright pass for shared screenshots, 98% generic + 2% product overlay, hint mechanism for dead-end navigation\n- Feedback loop (eval \u2192 refine \u2192 re-eval, max 3 iterations) is still in progress\n\n**[UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md)** \u2014 the scoring backbone.\n- 4 dimensions scored 0\u20132 each (8 total): Completeness, Usability, Feasibility, Fidelity Match\n- Pass threshold: 6+ with no zeros\n- Usability dimension uses Nielsen's 10 heuristics\n- One scorer agent per dimension for deterministic/auditable scores\n\n**[Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md)** \u2014 the methodology foundation.\n- Compared Cursor, Claude Code, Gemini Flash/Pro, and ChatGPT on heuristic eval quality using Kubernetes/OpenShift UI screens\n- Evaluation dimensions: analysis quality, depth, specificity, structure, hallucinations, unique insights\n- Key finding: the \"jagged edge\" \u2014 AI capabilities are uneven; which tool to trust for evaluation isn't obvious\n- Deliverables are Google Doc + Slides linked in the page\n\n---\n\n## Related Context\n\n**[Standup \u2014 June 29](standup-2026-06-29.md)**\n- Usability testing RFC was approved by the team\n- 2 automated usability testing agents currently in development (you + Yahav)\n- Yingzhao iterating on usability comparison approach; Yahav assigned to publish a formal proposal for usability testing in the AI dev lifecycle\n\n**[RH AI-First UX \u2014 June 25](rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-25.md)**\n- Testing fragmentation flagged: Yonyi's team, your evaluator, and heuristic analysis skills are all doing different things with no canonical standard\n- Yahav assigned to draft a unified usability testing proposal (dimensions + requirements)\n\n**[Andy/Evan \u2014 June 29](andy-evan-2026-06-29.md)**\n- \"X-ray vs blind\" evaluation modes discussed \u2014 whether the agent evaluates with code visibility or from a user-perspective-only view\n- \"Auto-fix vs Report-only\" modes in development for managing regressions\n- Report UX: avoid cockpit density; prioritize errors top-left; overview-first with drill-down\n- Future: \"Leaderboard of Pain\" \u2014 synthesizes cross-report research insights into top user pain points\n\n---\n\n## Knowledge Gaps\n\nYour wiki doesn't yet cover:\n- The content of Yahav's unified testing proposal (once drafted)\n- The Avenir-UX and UXCascade papers referenced in the Evaluator page (methodology detail)\n- Yonyi's team's testing approach (mentioned as a fragmentation point but not documented)\n- What the approved RFC actually specifies"}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 2013, "cache_read_input_tokens": 41914, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 2013, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 1}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "f9a3ce62-434a-4f59-920a-2c5c141fc64e", "uuid": "0b367487-b432-4d07-8ea9-4ea8d29186c1", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcrjFaNs7JMXnd4cggzj5", "timestamp": "2026-07-09T15:35:34.655Z"}
